reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I got this fan almost 3 years ago for a car camping trip. it works great, has battery life to run all night on a single charge (even on higher speeds), the light has come in handy plenty.I haven't camped with it in the past year, but still gets used often enough- I set it up in front of a window when the weather is nice, by the bathroom door when I shower to keep the mirror from fogging up, and just for white noise sometimes.I haven't been gentle on it either, at some point I dropped it to where the fan cover came off and couldn't be bothered to re-manage the cables for the motion sensor i dont use- so i ripped them out and it works fine still lol.great fan!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Powerful and long lasting
reviews.reviewText: I can't believe I spent $50 for a fan... but for baseball tournaments in Texas, this was worth it! Very powerful air flow and I ran it for almost 6 hours and it never lost more than 1 dot on the battery status. I haven't needed the light but its definitely better than the ones on the fans that I returned. The others had it like a spotlight and if you're using the fan then you'd be blinded by the flashlight. This one is nice and bright and on the back so it illuminates like a lantern more than a flashlight and wont be straight in your eyes. I've only had it a month, so hopefully it'll be just as good long term!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great addition to my desk top needs
reviews.reviewText: Provides a cool breeze in the direction needed on my desk during hot weather. Easy to use and operate.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 100 % worth every penny and then some
reviews.reviewText: Best rechargeable fan I've ever owned. This thing is POWERFUL. It does a better job of cooling me off than ever our ceiling fans. It has several settings and lasts nearly an entire day on high at Disney world. We would not have survived Disney in June without it lol. We attached it to the stroller and multiple times we ended up with a line of people behind us asking if they could "soak up our air" lol! It is a bit bulkier than some of the other rechargeable fans, but not much bigger than a pair of men's shoes. My only complaint is that the rubber part of the clamp broke after several days of use, making it very difficult to get it to stay attached to the stroller. Otherwise a year later, it's still going strong.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great little fan!
reviews.reviewText: Not supposed to “love” inanimate objects but when you are camping on a hot, muggy, Florida summer night and a breath of air comes to you, it feels a lot like love. I have had this fan for a year & a half now. It kicks out a large amount of air and light. It can be hung via clamp or hook, so good in a couple of different places for me. AND it holds a charge all night. I’ve had fans that pushed a sufficient amount of air before but they lose power about 2:00 AM and that is just not enough. This little beast is my best camping friend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2022
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Had an opolar 8" round clip fan but needed to upgrade to a strong blowing fan that would last up to 12 hr so I bought this one. Battery life on highest setting does last me 11+ hr and it's not as loud. Only con compared to my 8" round fan is that it's not 100% 360° due to it not being able to turn in the direction of the clip (where you would mount it on) and in some cases that's the only place available due to the space. I've came across that already but I just shift the fan because I have enough room to swivel it in the direction towards the clip.

reviews.reviewText: I use this fan on my golf cart. Very high cfm and quiet. Use at highest speed during hot Florida rounds. Battery lasted 2+ rounds. Still had plenty of juice after 8 total hours.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024

reviews.reviewText: tengo un año y medio usandolo y la verdad muy satisfecho, en el trabajo lo uso de 3 a 5 hrs diarias en velocidad 2 y me llega a tardar hasta 8 o 9 veces usandolo ( 3 a 5 hrs diarias), antes de volver a cargar, sin mencionar que en velocidad 2 ya es suficiente para mantener fresco, ni se diga en velocidad 3 o 4 que es mucho aire para un ventilador pequeño, cuando se va la luz, lo uso para dormir a velocidad 2 ( las 8 o 9 hrs de sueño)
Good range of powers and solid battery life, plus sturdy build and options to hang, clip and stand up
A pesar de que si hace algo de ruido la cantidad de aire que mueve es casi sorprendente para el tamaño del ventilador, ademas que por su bateria lo puedes acomodar donde quieras, muy recomendado!.

La realidad es que cumple con lo que ofrece, la batería dura muchas horas. Es silencioso en las velocidades bajas que son en las que casi siempre lo tenemos. Una nota es que el cargador (no incluido) se caliente mucho, habrá que probar con otros.
Se me hace práctico y funcional
